we have a tab of buttons
by clicking on a tab we want to display the content related to the tab
also we want the current tab to have a active bgcolor
HTML:
add a div element with classname
    inside it add buttons with classname and onclick attribute
add 3 div element with same classname and diff ids
    inside each add h3 and p tag with its contents

CSS:
button container div
    add hidden overflow prop
    add bgcolor
    add border
button
    add left float prop
    add inherited bgcolor
    add padding
    add pointer cursor
    add no border
    add no outline
    add transition
button on hover
    add bgcolor
button which is active
    add bgcolor
tabcontent
    add none display
    add border
    add padding
    remove top border
JS:
    write a function with args event, cityName
        set display prop of tabcontent to none
        remove active classname from button
        set display prop to block
        add the active class to currentTarget